2
00:01:07.594 --> 00:01:12.033
(Doom at Your Service)

3
00:01:12.300 --> 00:01:15.324
(All characters. locations. organizations. religions. )

4
00:01:15.325 --> 00:01:17.796
(and incidents in this drama are fictional.)

5
00:01:19.235 --> 00:01:21.765
(Episode 9)

6
00:01:21.766 --> 00:01:22.976
Thanks for the food!

7
00:01:42.955 --> 00:01:46.665
At one point. I wanted to be one of them.

8
00:01:48.565 --> 00:01:50.665
- Here. - Hey. you know what?

9
00:01:50.966 --> 00:01:52.495
You should try the drink.

10
00:01:52.735 --> 00:01:54.405
You might like it.

11
00:01:54.406 --> 00:01:55.735
All right.

12
00:01:56.675 --> 00:01:58.476
You're pretty good for a first-timer.

13
00:01:59.546 --> 00:02:00.646
You know?

14
00:02:02.076 --> 00:02:03.645
I wanted to eat just like them.

15
00:02:11.916 --> 00:02:13.485
And I wanted to fall asleep like them.

16
00:02:27.636 --> 00:02:29.834
- Hello. - Hello.

17
00:02:29.835 --> 00:02:31.734
- Mom! - Mommy!

18
00:02:31.735 --> 00:02:33.276
- Mom! - Dad!

19
00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:35.276
Daddy!

20
00:02:38.016 --> 00:02:39.516
I wanted to have compassion...

21
00:02:40.315 --> 00:02:41.645
and love like them.

22
00:02:50.425 --> 00:02:52.796
But being one of them was impossible.

23
00:02:55.365 --> 00:02:56.766
They always leave.

24
00:02:57.796 --> 00:03:00.636
They always have a place to be...

25
00:03:01.835 --> 00:03:03.076
unlike me.

26
00:03:11.272 --> 00:03:15.872
(Bean Sprout Gukbap Restaurant)

27
00:03:20.583 --> 00:03:22.583
(For Rent)

28
00:03:31.844 --> 00:03:33.214
That's when I realized it.

29
00:03:35.133 --> 00:03:36.703
I had no place to be.

30
00:03:37.032 --> 00:03:39.133
There was no end to this life.

31
00:03:40.133 --> 00:03:42.103
So I could never become one of them.

32
00:03:53.282 --> 00:03:55.083
My job...

33
00:03:55.782 --> 00:03:57.483
is to merely watch them.

34
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:03.863
So choose.

35
00:04:05.462 --> 00:04:06.733
Choose yourself and the world.

36
00:04:20.212 --> 00:04:23.212
All I can do is watch.

37
00:04:31.722 --> 00:04:33.591
You darn brat! Stop right there!

38
00:04:33.592 --> 00:04:35.292
How do you expect me to stop when you're running after me?

39
00:04:35.293 --> 00:04:36.992
I won't stop.

40
00:04:37.522 --> 00:04:38.562
You little brat.

41
00:05:04.423 --> 00:05:05.423
Hey.

42
00:05:08.692 --> 00:05:10.763
I'm sorry for showing up like this all of a sudden.

43
00:05:19.702 --> 00:05:20.733
Who's here?

44
00:05:21.603 --> 00:05:23.942
Wait for me on the first floor. I'll be right there.

45
00:05:27.043 --> 00:05:28.512
Let me know if you heard that.

46
00:06:02.343 --> 00:06:04.713
I'll be right back.

47
00:06:06.382 --> 00:06:07.382
Here.

48
00:06:13.023 --> 00:06:14.292
If you're leaving because of me. I'll leave.

49
00:06:14.293 --> 00:06:15.821
I'm sorry. That's not it.

50
00:06:15.822 --> 00:06:16.923
Is there something wrong?

51
00:06:19.863 --> 00:06:22.463
He's here. Lee Hyun Kyu.

52
00:06:25.163 --> 00:06:28.201
I'm sorry. but can you wait a bit...

53
00:06:28.202 --> 00:06:30.403
before you come outside?

54
00:06:31.403 --> 00:06:33.442
- I just don't want... - I understand.

55
00:06:39.543 --> 00:06:40.582
I'm sorry.

56
00:06:52.593 --> 00:06:54.692
She didn't have to apologize. but it does feel...

57
00:06:55.562 --> 00:06:56.632
a little weird.

58
00:07:12.343 --> 00:07:13.983
Who told you my address?

59
00:07:15.613 --> 00:07:16.852
I asked around.

60
00:07:16.853 --> 00:07:18.581
Did you think it'd be okay to just come by...

61
00:07:18.582 --> 00:07:20.223
just because someone told you my address?

62
00:07:20.553 --> 00:07:21.653
No.

63
00:07:22.322 --> 00:07:24.792
It seemed like the wrong thing to do.

64
00:07:24.793 --> 00:07:26.762
- Then why did you come? - I couldn't help it.

65
00:07:29.832 --> 00:07:31.033
I missed you.

66
00:07:33.002 --> 00:07:34.872
I came to Korea because I missed you.

67
00:07:35.502 --> 00:07:37.442
And I went to the reunion for the same reason.

68
00:07:40.372 --> 00:07:42.072
I came here to tell you that.

69
00:07:46.343 --> 00:07:47.853
You always do things however you like.

70
00:07:53.252 --> 00:07:54.723
- Hello. - Hey.

71
00:07:56.223 --> 00:07:57.663
You just do everything however you like. don't you?

72
00:07:59.622 --> 00:08:01.962
How could you not tell me that you're leaving to study abroad?

73
00:08:01.963 --> 00:08:04.103
I can't believe you made me come all the way here.

74
00:08:05.502 --> 00:08:07.772
- I'm sorry. - Why didn't you text me back?

75
00:08:07.773 --> 00:08:09.033
Are you really going to break up?

76
00:08:10.273 --> 00:08:13.372
I just felt really sorry.

77
00:08:14.043 --> 00:08:16.212
Then you should've texted me back.

78
00:08:16.213 --> 00:08:18.142
If you felt sorry. you should've met up with me.

79
00:08:20.553 --> 00:08:21.582
I'm really sorry.

80
00:08:22.252 --> 00:08:23.322
You're always like this.

81
00:08:24.082 --> 00:08:27.321
I liked you first. and I like you more than you like me.

82
00:08:27.322 --> 00:08:29.053
You know that. You're totally aware of it.

83
00:08:33.663 --> 00:08:34.663
Forget it.

84
00:08:36.392 --> 00:08:38.702
That's not it. Let me explain.

85
00:08:40.572 --> 00:08:43.242
I may be going abroad to study. but I never said I wanted to end it.

86
00:08:48.173 --> 00:08:49.273
Look at yourself.

87
00:08:49.913 --> 00:08:51.242
You're being selfish again.

88
00:08:53.252 --> 00:08:55.452
I bet you thought I didn't have the guts to break up.

89
00:08:56.952 --> 00:08:58.552
You kept dragging things on.

90
00:08:58.553 --> 00:09:01.292
and we eventually broke up without even talking about it.

91
00:09:01.293 --> 00:09:02.593
I always regretted it.

92
00:09:03.622 --> 00:09:04.962
I was too young back then.

93
00:09:04.963 --> 00:09:08.191
I know how it feels to blindly wait in front of someone's house...

94
00:09:08.192 --> 00:09:09.463
because I've also done it before.

95
00:09:10.103 --> 00:09:11.931
You wonder what you're going to say when you meet them.

96
00:09:11.932 --> 00:09:12.932
but you can't come up with anything.

97
00:09:13.603 --> 00:09:14.773
But even so.

98
00:09:16.803 --> 00:09:18.303
I couldn't help but just wait.

99
00:09:19.072 --> 00:09:20.113
I just waited.

100
00:09:21.413 --> 00:09:23.682
- Ji Na. - But you're not like me.

101
00:09:25.582 --> 00:09:26.582
But then again.

102
00:09:27.783 --> 00:09:29.353
I never got to meet you.

103
00:09:30.452 --> 00:09:31.722
But you did.

104
00:09:35.092 --> 00:09:36.763
You should've shown up like this back then.

105
00:09:38.623 --> 00:09:40.132
You're too late. It's been nine years.

106
00:09:40.133 --> 00:09:42.293
I know. I'm not trying to do anything. I just...

107
00:09:42.592 --> 00:09:45.062
I just wanted to answer your question.

108
00:09:45.432 --> 00:09:47.503
But if you think I'm only complicating things.

109
00:09:47.873 --> 00:09:49.072
just forget about it.

110
00:09:50.442 --> 00:09:51.772
I'm sorry. Don't let it bother you.

111
00:09:51.773 --> 00:09:52.873
I can't.

112
00:09:53.243 --> 00:09:55.543
You'll be on my mind for a while now that I've met you today.

113
00:09:56.682 --> 00:09:57.712
Look at me now.

114
00:09:58.612 --> 00:10:00.653
Even now. I'm sitting right in front of you.

115
00:10:03.553 --> 00:10:04.923
Whenever I'm with you.

116
00:10:05.682 --> 00:10:08.023
it takes me back to the past.

117
00:10:10.263 --> 00:10:11.623
I was always wet.

118
00:10:12.493 --> 00:10:14.692
The day I saw you at the pool and the day I waited in the rain.

119
00:10:16.133 --> 00:10:17.303
Liking you...

120
00:10:18.803 --> 00:10:20.533
felt so wet and damp for me.

121
00:10:21.803 --> 00:10:23.602
Although it might've been soft and fuzzy for you.

122
00:10:25.643 --> 00:10:27.273
I'm not so sure if I want to go back...

123
00:10:28.972 --> 00:10:30.013
to those days.

124
00:10:33.952 --> 00:10:35.612
I still liked everything about you.

125
00:10:39.452 --> 00:10:40.553
Regardless of all that happened.

126
00:10:42.993 --> 00:10:44.062
I still liked you.

127
00:11:03.643 --> 00:11:05.743
Auntie. calm down!

128
00:11:05.783 --> 00:11:08.581
- How do you expect me to calm down? - Sun Kyung. that punk.

129
00:11:08.582 --> 00:11:10.123
Who am I going to blame?

130
00:11:11.852 --> 00:11:12.923
Auntie.

131
00:11:13.222 --> 00:11:14.553
Auntie. stop.

132
00:11:15.523 --> 00:11:17.692
Auntie. wait. Wait.

133
00:11:17.793 --> 00:11:20.361
- Get over here. Come here. - No. wait. Calm down.

134
00:11:20.362 --> 00:11:22.592
I didn't do it on purpose.

135
00:11:22.763 --> 00:11:24.632
Get over here while I'm being nice.

136
00:11:24.633 --> 00:11:27.572
You're not being nice right now.

137
00:11:31.903 --> 00:11:32.972
Auntie.

138
00:11:34.442 --> 00:11:37.283
Auntie. Auntie. are you okay? Auntie.

139
00:11:39.043 --> 00:11:40.311
- I got you. - Auntie.

140
00:11:40.312 --> 00:11:43.622
This isn't fair. That's cheating.

141
00:11:43.623 --> 00:11:45.682
You're the one who cheated first.

142
00:11:45.783 --> 00:11:48.721
No. wait. Let me go.

143
00:11:48.722 --> 00:11:51.321
- My gosh. I'm so exhausted. - Please let go.

144
00:11:51.322 --> 00:11:52.562
Auntie. please!

145
00:12:05.972 --> 00:12:07.143
Sit down.

146
00:12:07.342 --> 00:12:09.212
I don't want to sit on the floor.

147
00:12:13.582 --> 00:12:15.311
He can be very American at times.

148
00:12:15.312 --> 00:12:17.923
He doesn't do it often. but he did it just now.

149
00:12:24.962 --> 00:12:27.393
Let me finally introduce myself. Dong Kyung's boyfriend.

150
00:12:27.962 --> 00:12:31.102
My name is Kang Soo Ja. I'm Dong Kyung's aunt.

151
00:12:31.732 --> 00:12:34.403
Yes. she's my aunt. Kang Soo Ja.

152
00:12:34.633 --> 00:12:35.773
"Boyfriend"?

153
00:12:36.743 --> 00:12:38.302
I heard a lot about you.

154
00:12:38.303 --> 00:12:40.243
You heard a lot about him? From whom?

155
00:12:50.753 --> 00:12:52.282
Sun Kyung. that punk.

156
00:12:52.283 --> 00:12:54.622
I'm sorry for what happened earlier.

157
00:12:54.623 --> 00:12:55.993
I bet you were shocked.

158
00:12:56.222 --> 00:12:58.663
It's okay. Don't worry about it.

159
00:12:59.592 --> 00:13:01.932
By the way. where do you live?

160
00:13:02.432 --> 00:13:05.562
It's very late.

161
00:13:05.862 --> 00:13:06.872
I live...

162
00:13:06.873 --> 00:13:10.033
Yes. she's right. It's really late.

163
00:13:10.173 --> 00:13:11.841
- You should go home. - But you told me to sit down.

164
00:13:11.842 --> 00:13:13.942
It's time for you to get up. Hurry.

165
00:13:15.572 --> 00:13:18.042
What? I know. right? It's such a relief.

166
00:13:18.043 --> 00:13:19.842
You can still take the bus.

167
00:13:19.942 --> 00:13:22.112
You should get going now.

168
00:13:23.383 --> 00:13:25.652
I'd ask you to stay and drink with me.

169
00:13:25.653 --> 00:13:28.293
But as you can see. our family is going through something important.

170
00:13:29.317 --> 00:13:31.191
What? You're okay?

171
00:13:31.192 --> 00:13:33.691
Yes. of course. He says it's fine. Auntie. Wait.

172
00:13:33.692 --> 00:13:35.362
Here. Take this.

173
00:13:36.033 --> 00:13:37.962
Stop that. Get out.

174
00:13:38.362 --> 00:13:39.432
Go.

175
00:13:41.202 --> 00:13:42.673
Call me later.

176
00:13:43.203 --> 00:13:45.043
Bye! Okay!

177
00:13:50.114 --> 00:13:52.484
She's always so unpredictable.

178
00:14:15.573 --> 00:14:16.604
Auntie.

179
00:14:30.137 --> 00:14:32.108
I know how you feel.

180
00:14:34.137 --> 00:14:35.478
So I won't get mad.

181
00:14:38.507 --> 00:14:39.877
"I'll be a burden."

182
00:14:40.247 --> 00:14:41.478
"I'll be a nuisance."

183
00:14:42.547 --> 00:14:45.246
I know that's what you were thinking...

184
00:14:45.247 --> 00:14:46.517
and that's why you didn't call me.

185
00:14:51.287 --> 00:14:52.488
The colour is perfect.

186
00:14:53.627 --> 00:14:55.698
I bought it on sale last year. It's perfect.

187
00:14:56.897 --> 00:14:57.968
I'm glad I got it.

188
00:14:59.667 --> 00:15:01.968
You were like that since you were 10.

189
00:15:02.068 --> 00:15:03.497
You walked on eggshells around me...

190
00:15:03.738 --> 00:15:05.208
and acted like a guest.

191
00:15:06.007 --> 00:15:08.237
Why did you bother?

192
00:15:08.238 --> 00:15:09.577
You always did what you wanted.

193
00:15:09.578 --> 00:15:11.407
So why did you bother walking on eggshells?

194
00:15:11.978 --> 00:15:13.547
You create stress for no reason.

195
00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:15.678
How could you not get sick?

196
00:15:16.877 --> 00:15:17.948
Auntie.

197
00:15:19.247 --> 00:15:21.058
How long will you be polite?

198
00:15:24.257 --> 00:15:26.328
Are you a guest who dropped into my life?

199
00:15:28.757 --> 00:15:31.667
Anyway... Why is this hat so big?

200
00:15:32.127 --> 00:15:33.428
Is your head tiny?

201
00:15:35.238 --> 00:15:37.208
I thought it would fit.

202
00:15:40.478 --> 00:15:41.907
I'll give it to Sun Kyung.

203
00:15:43.377 --> 00:15:46.407
Hey. I bought a few summer dresses too.

204
00:15:46.647 --> 00:15:48.078
Do you want to try them on?

205
00:15:51.017 --> 00:15:54.357
I bought one here and there whenever I thought of you...

206
00:15:54.358 --> 00:15:55.988
when I was in Canada.

207
00:15:56.858 --> 00:15:58.728
You have to wear them all.

208
00:15:59.257 --> 00:16:01.058
I need to get my money's worth.

209
00:16:04.828 --> 00:16:08.068
That was my intent when I boarded that plane.

210
00:16:10.297 --> 00:16:13.037
So you have to get your act together.

211
00:16:16.838 --> 00:16:19.007
Don't give this to Sun Kyung. It's mine.

212
00:16:21.178 --> 00:16:24.588
Gosh. You're greedy about clothes just like your mom.

213
00:16:25.147 --> 00:16:27.787
Do you know how much of my stuff she took from me?

214
00:16:29.517 --> 00:16:32.887
That's why I didn't want to take your life from you.

215
00:16:38.098 --> 00:16:39.767
You never took it.

216
00:16:41.198 --> 00:16:42.598
I gave it to you willingly.

217
00:16:46.907 --> 00:16:48.438
Because I wanted to.

218
00:17:11.280 --> 00:17:13.179
(Na Ji Na - Did you get home safely?)

219
00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:14.450
Did you get home safely?

220
00:17:15.151 --> 00:17:16.810
I was too out of it earlier.

221
00:17:17.981 --> 00:17:20.121
(Na Ji Na - Did you get home safely?)

222
00:17:26.920 --> 00:17:28.491
- You're back. - Yes.

223
00:17:29.361 --> 00:17:31.131
- Were you in the shower? - Yes.

224
00:17:31.830 --> 00:17:32.901
You should wash up too.

225
00:17:33.460 --> 00:17:35.101
Okay. Rest up.

226
00:17:36.231 --> 00:17:37.300
Rest up.

227
00:18:26.220 --> 00:18:34.061
(Ms. Soo Ja)

228
00:18:41.631 --> 00:18:42.631
Hello?

229
00:18:43.301 --> 00:18:44.341
Hey.

230
00:18:44.740 --> 00:18:46.440
You know how to answer the phone?

231
00:18:47.811 --> 00:18:49.641
- I know how to hang up too. - Hey.

232
00:18:51.641 --> 00:18:53.439
I'm calling in secret.

233
00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:55.081
so don't make me yell.

234
00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:02.051
What are you doing? Are you home?

235
00:19:03.291 --> 00:19:04.291
Why?

236
00:19:04.690 --> 00:19:07.490
I'm just curious. You always slept with me.

237
00:19:07.930 --> 00:19:09.660
You're hesitant only with certain words.

238
00:19:10.260 --> 00:19:12.500
Otherwise. you're so free with your words.

239
00:19:14.031 --> 00:19:16.601
Do I? Anyway...

240
00:19:17.770 --> 00:19:18.770
Yes.

241
00:19:19.641 --> 00:19:21.041
Is that all you can say?

242
00:19:21.770 --> 00:19:22.811
Yes.

243
00:19:23.641 --> 00:19:24.740
Darn it.

244
00:19:30.450 --> 00:19:34.051
Your aunt looks a lot like your mom.

245
00:19:35.490 --> 00:19:37.791
They don't just look alike. They look the same.

246
00:19:38.091 --> 00:19:39.391
They're twins.

247
00:19:40.260 --> 00:19:43.531
I feel like I'm looking at my mom when I see my aunt.

248
00:19:44.430 --> 00:19:46.000
I'd always look at her...

249
00:19:46.460 --> 00:19:48.729
and think that was what my mom probably looked like.

250
00:19:48.730 --> 00:19:52.041
I always thought that. but it was all I could do.

251
00:19:52.871 --> 00:19:54.910
But seeing her in person. I realized they were different.

252
00:19:55.740 --> 00:19:56.770
Thanks.

253
00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:04.720
I didn't get to say that.

254
00:20:05.551 --> 00:20:09.121
Thank you for letting me see my mom and dad.

255
00:20:12.561 --> 00:20:13.561
Sure.

256
00:20:14.660 --> 00:20:17.360
And I'll think hard about my wish...

257
00:20:17.361 --> 00:20:18.631
for myself.

258
00:20:23.131 --> 00:20:24.170
Okay.

259
00:20:25.440 --> 00:20:26.900
Is that all you can say?

260
00:20:26.901 --> 00:20:28.240
I can say. "Good night." too.

261
00:20:33.341 --> 00:20:34.381
Good night.

262
00:20:37.111 --> 00:20:39.519
This so new and awkward.

263
00:20:39.520 --> 00:20:40.920
doing this over the phone.

264
00:20:42.250 --> 00:20:43.621
- Bye. - Wait.

265
00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:45.190
What?

266
00:20:45.621 --> 00:20:48.930
You said you'd do pretty much anything for me. right?

267
00:20:50.631 --> 00:20:52.000
So I was thinking...

268
00:20:52.861 --> 00:20:55.970
May I ask you for a favour?

269
00:21:05.143 --> 00:21:07.011
A new drug was confirmed to be safe...

270
00:21:07.012 --> 00:21:08.511
and is currently in clinical trials.

271
00:21:08.512 --> 00:21:10.153
and they're looking for more volunteers.

272
00:21:11.823 --> 00:21:13.051
Her name is on the list.

273
00:21:13.052 --> 00:21:14.693
so we're waiting to hear back.

274
00:21:15.693 --> 00:21:19.221
When can we begin treatment?

275
00:21:19.222 --> 00:21:21.261
We need to wait for the blood work.

276
00:21:21.262 --> 00:21:22.762
so it'll take about two weeks.

277
00:21:24.232 --> 00:21:25.432
If she qualifies.

278
00:21:25.433 --> 00:21:27.032
she'll have to come in periodically.

279
00:21:27.433 --> 00:21:28.772
See?

280
00:21:29.103 --> 00:21:32.202
Let's relax and wait patiently.

281
00:21:33.373 --> 00:21:34.443
Are you sure...

282
00:21:35.073 --> 00:21:38.482
she doesn't need to be hospitalized right away?

283
00:21:38.843 --> 00:21:40.482
Yes. I am.

284
00:21:41.212 --> 00:21:44.452
You're saying there's hope. right?

285
00:21:45.653 --> 00:21:46.853
Can she live?

286
00:21:47.593 --> 00:21:50.353
Yes. I'm in the process of saving her.

287
00:21:59.732 --> 00:22:03.472
Didn't you say yesterday that your boyfriend is a doctor too?

288
00:22:03.702 --> 00:22:06.042
- Where does he work? - Him?

289
00:22:06.573 --> 00:22:08.712
He works...

290
00:22:09.373 --> 00:22:11.212
in the US. He's an American doctor.

291
00:22:11.613 --> 00:22:13.712
I see. He's in the US.

292
00:22:14.252 --> 00:22:16.252
That's why you said at times that he was American.

293
00:22:16.583 --> 00:22:17.883
Yes. that's right.

294
00:22:19.683 --> 00:22:21.892
Although your boyfriend is...

295
00:22:21.893 --> 00:22:24.193
very slightly less attractive...

296
00:22:24.792 --> 00:22:26.722
than your doctor...

297
00:22:26.962 --> 00:22:28.093
He's less attractive?

298
00:22:29.032 --> 00:22:31.731
Who cares about his looks?

299
00:22:31.732 --> 00:22:33.232
As long as he's a good person.

300
00:22:33.833 --> 00:22:36.573
Sun Kyung told me that he's a very nice guy.

301
00:22:37.287 --> 00:22:39.455
But you know. I wouldn't say...

302
00:22:39.456 --> 00:22:42.885
he's ugly or anything like that.

303
00:22:42.886 --> 00:22:46.297
My gosh. You're totally into him.

304
00:22:48.527 --> 00:22:50.596
Then. let me go. pick my Canadian husband.

305
00:22:50.597 --> 00:22:52.436
and drop him off at a hotel.

306
00:22:52.696 --> 00:22:54.537
Meanwhile. you can hang out with your American boyfriend.

307
00:22:55.007 --> 00:22:59.107
Gosh. You guys didn't have to come back to Korea.

308
00:22:59.537 --> 00:23:02.146
Don't you know how much Kevin adores you guys?

309
00:23:02.676 --> 00:23:04.817
Don't say stuff like that. Kevin will be disappointed.

310
00:23:05.277 --> 00:23:07.076
I could barely stop him from buying a house in Seoul.

311
00:23:07.077 --> 00:23:08.916
so we could all live together.

312
00:23:16.886 --> 00:23:19.497
I'll be back. I won't be gone for long.

313
00:23:20.456 --> 00:23:21.497
Okay.

314
00:23:45.357 --> 00:23:48.087
- I want my cell phone. - I see.

315
00:23:50.087 --> 00:23:51.097
Gosh.

316
00:23:51.656 --> 00:23:52.896
- All good? - Yes.

317
00:23:53.396 --> 00:23:55.166
- Bye. - Where are you going?

318
00:23:56.597 --> 00:23:57.597
You said you're all good.

319
00:23:57.966 --> 00:24:01.206
I'm all good with the phone. And I'm not done with you yet.

320
00:24:04.277 --> 00:24:05.277
Here.

321
00:24:07.706 --> 00:24:09.576
- What's this? - It's a cell phone.

322
00:24:09.577 --> 00:24:10.676
You've never seen one before?

323
00:24:10.747 --> 00:24:12.646
- No. I saw it yesterday. - Gosh.

324
00:24:12.916 --> 00:24:14.287
Come on. Take it already.

325
00:24:15.386 --> 00:24:17.487
No. I'm asking you why I need this.

326
00:24:19.216 --> 00:24:22.026
There might be another incident similar to yesterday's again. Okay?

327
00:24:22.027 --> 00:24:24.256
I have a plan. Okay?

328
00:24:24.257 --> 00:24:26.827
Or were you excited that we talked on the phone before going to sleep?

329
00:24:28.267 --> 00:24:31.767
Well. that's partially true.

330
00:24:32.237 --> 00:24:33.296
Who's paying for this?

331
00:24:33.297 --> 00:24:35.566
That brings me to my next question. What's your bank account number?

332
00:24:35.567 --> 00:24:37.007
Or tell me your card number.

333
00:24:38.337 --> 00:24:39.706
Is this phone even working?

334
00:24:40.037 --> 00:24:41.206
Goodness.

335
00:24:42.706 --> 00:24:43.746
Here.

336
00:24:43.747 --> 00:24:44.876
(Human)

337
00:24:52.787 --> 00:24:54.757
(Dong Kyung)

338
00:24:55.126 --> 00:24:58.126
I didn't include our last names because full names sound distant.

339
00:24:59.327 --> 00:25:02.766
All right. We have each other's numbers.

340
00:25:02.767 --> 00:25:03.896
What should we do next?

341
00:25:08.007 --> 00:25:09.737
(Human)

342
00:25:11.077 --> 00:25:12.077
What are you doing?

343
00:25:12.376 --> 00:25:13.406
Answer it.

344
00:25:16.706 --> 00:25:17.747
Are you free?

345
00:25:19.547 --> 00:25:21.487
Isn't this the next step after getting a girl's number?

346
00:25:23.087 --> 00:25:24.517
What if I'm free?

347
00:25:24.987 --> 00:25:26.156
Let's hang out.

348
00:25:42.237 --> 00:25:44.837
What's this? Why are we here?

349
00:25:46.876 --> 00:25:49.206
What is it? Is this a present for me?

350
00:25:49.946 --> 00:25:52.277
- No. that's your work. - Work?

351
00:25:52.476 --> 00:25:55.047
You've gotten materialistic lately. Do you want a present from me?

352
00:25:55.547 --> 00:25:56.946
Gosh.

353
00:26:11.267 --> 00:26:14.507
Grandma. Then. my teacher isn't coming?

354
00:26:15.767 --> 00:26:19.376
I heard that there's no boat coming to the island.

355
00:26:19.876 --> 00:26:23.107
I don't think your teacher will make it today.

356
00:26:23.277 --> 00:26:24.746
Then. I can't have my graduation ceremony?

357
00:26:24.747 --> 00:26:28.247
You and I will have your graduation ceremony together.

358
00:26:28.446 --> 00:26:31.456
You already have your diploma right here.

359
00:26:31.886 --> 00:26:34.527
I want to get the diploma from my teacher.

360
00:26:40.626 --> 00:26:43.266
- Sir. - Sir.

361
00:26:43.267 --> 00:26:45.636
My gosh. I thought you wouldn't be able to make it.

362
00:26:47.866 --> 00:26:50.607
I ought to come today. It's the school's last graduation.

363
00:26:55.876 --> 00:26:57.247
Who are you?

364
00:26:57.376 --> 00:26:58.376
What?

365
00:26:58.747 --> 00:27:01.186
Well...

366
00:27:02.646 --> 00:27:04.385
She came from Seoul to take photos today.

367
00:27:04.386 --> 00:27:06.857
From Seoul? She flew here?

368
00:27:08.156 --> 00:27:09.186
Yes.

369
00:27:09.926 --> 00:27:11.557
I'm here to take photos.

370
00:27:14.366 --> 00:27:17.466
All right. Here it goes.

371
00:27:17.896 --> 00:27:19.966
In 1. 2.

372
00:27:20.097 --> 00:27:23.837
(Diploma)

373
00:27:28.946 --> 00:27:32.476
Then. this school will disappear?

374
00:27:33.876 --> 00:27:35.817
There won't be any students coming to the school anymore.

375
00:27:36.247 --> 00:27:37.787
And there aren't any teachers who would teach here.

376
00:27:38.287 --> 00:27:40.386
Where's the real teacher?

377
00:27:41.926 --> 00:27:43.787
He's probably headed somewhere.

378
00:27:44.857 --> 00:27:47.726
- Where? Is he having a dream? - No.

379
00:27:48.200 --> 00:27:49.930
He's headed to the opposite direction of life.

380
00:27:51.049 --> 00:27:52.250
By now.

381
00:27:53.237 --> 00:27:55.237
he could have arrived at the garden.

382
00:28:08.116 --> 00:28:09.216
You know. that girl?

383
00:28:10.886 --> 00:28:12.716
The girl at the garden.

384
00:28:14.857 --> 00:28:16.787
I've seen her at the hospital too.

385
00:28:17.626 --> 00:28:19.726
She was wearing a patient gown that time.

386
00:28:21.767 --> 00:28:22.797
She's sick.

387
00:28:24.737 --> 00:28:25.737
She is?

388
00:28:27.097 --> 00:28:28.107
She's always sick.

389
00:28:28.807 --> 00:28:31.436
She's always born sick. suffers in pain. and dies.

390
00:28:32.636 --> 00:28:35.645
And she's reborn again just to go through the same pain.

391
00:28:35.646 --> 00:28:36.976
Then. she dies again.

392
00:28:39.277 --> 00:28:41.716
That's how she maintains the world.

393
00:28:42.787 --> 00:28:45.616
She suffers in pain for all the sins in the world and dies.

394
00:28:49.057 --> 00:28:50.257
That's the duty of a deity.

395
00:28:54.966 --> 00:28:57.166
I saw her repeat that many times for a long time.

396
00:29:00.237 --> 00:29:03.067
I thought I had the most miserable life.

397
00:29:04.237 --> 00:29:05.876
My pain was nothing compared to hers.

398
00:29:08.406 --> 00:29:11.047
If there was nothing in the world from the beginning.

399
00:29:12.047 --> 00:29:13.976
would the world be a peaceful place?

400
00:29:15.587 --> 00:29:19.156
If nothing ever happened in the world.

401
00:29:25.357 --> 00:29:26.497
Don't move.

402
00:29:27.249 --> 00:29:29.249
What? Why?

403
00:29:45.517 --> 00:29:47.546
You didn't move for a second. And during that one second.

404
00:29:47.547 --> 00:29:49.686
nothing in the world was destroyed.

405
00:29:51.047 --> 00:29:53.817
It was the world you wanted.

406
00:29:58.057 --> 00:29:59.297
It's odd. isn't it?

407
00:30:00.097 --> 00:30:01.827
During that one second.

408
00:30:02.966 --> 00:30:05.037
my time stood still.

409
00:30:09.837 --> 00:30:13.577
(Kang Soo Ah)

410
00:30:14.646 --> 00:30:16.347
You're still beautiful.

411
00:30:19.817 --> 00:30:21.317
I'm the only one ageing.

412
00:30:24.557 --> 00:30:27.757
You're the one who should address me as the elder sister now.

413
00:30:35.297 --> 00:30:36.366
Soo Ah.

414
00:30:40.067 --> 00:30:41.466
I know you miss her.

415
00:30:43.267 --> 00:30:45.277
but please be patient a bit longer.

416
00:30:48.906 --> 00:30:50.107
Just a bit longer.

417
00:30:52.077 --> 00:30:53.876
Let her stay here a bit longer.

418
00:30:56.116 --> 00:30:57.847
I'm talking about Dong Kyung.

419
00:31:07.696 --> 00:31:09.767
One thing I learned in life is...

420
00:31:10.166 --> 00:31:13.635
that we can't use the word. "forever". for something...

421
00:31:13.636 --> 00:31:15.206
that is still happening.

422
00:31:16.166 --> 00:31:19.936
Loving someone forever is nearly impossible.

423
00:31:20.277 --> 00:31:24.347
But losing someone forever is possible.

424
00:31:28.017 --> 00:31:31.987
But we always live for things that don't last forever.

425
00:31:32.357 --> 00:31:34.756
For example. dreams are one of them.

426
00:31:34.757 --> 00:31:36.557
Two cups of latte are ready.

427
00:31:37.527 --> 00:31:39.696
- Thank you. - Thank you.

428
00:31:41.726 --> 00:31:43.196
- This is good. - Really?

429
00:31:47.636 --> 00:31:52.236
Or things like memories or regrets.

430
00:31:52.237 --> 00:31:54.277
("Second First Love". Lee Hyun Kyu)

431
00:31:57.476 --> 00:31:59.277
(Lee Hyun)

432
00:32:02.116 --> 00:32:06.415
Or some live for love or other people.

433
00:32:06.416 --> 00:32:07.885
(Human)

434
00:32:07.886 --> 00:32:09.656
The Korean words. "human". and "love". look similar.

435
00:32:10.152 --> 00:32:13.582
I shouldn't have given you such a name.

436
00:32:17.292 --> 00:32:19.993
Come out. I want to do something with you.

437
00:32:23.636 --> 00:32:25.507
Why am I here?

438
00:32:25.537 --> 00:32:28.675
- I've made up my mind today. - For what?

439
00:32:28.676 --> 00:32:30.346
I'm determined to spend money today.

440
00:32:30.347 --> 00:32:32.246
I've never done this in my life.

441
00:32:32.247 --> 00:32:33.715
So I need you.

442
00:32:33.716 --> 00:32:34.716
Why do you need me?

443
00:32:34.916 --> 00:32:36.945
I want you to watch me splurge.

444
00:32:36.946 --> 00:32:38.156
Make it fun for me.

445
00:32:43.857 --> 00:32:44.956
Give me everything...

446
00:32:48.767 --> 00:32:49.866
from here to here.

447
00:32:50.797 --> 00:32:52.166
You want all this?

448
00:32:52.297 --> 00:32:54.666
Yes. In 270mm.

449
00:33:15.886 --> 00:33:16.926
Then just up to here.

450
00:33:23.626 --> 00:33:26.037
People only have two feet. Is it necessary to buy this many?

451
00:33:26.237 --> 00:33:28.465
It's one for every season.

452
00:33:28.466 --> 00:33:31.366
Sun Kyung's shoes wear out very easily.

453
00:33:31.807 --> 00:33:33.476
There's our next stop.

454
00:33:43.646 --> 00:33:45.715
Do you know what gift writers don't like to receive...

455
00:33:45.716 --> 00:33:47.386
but end up receiving the most?

456
00:33:47.757 --> 00:33:49.386
- What is it? - Fountain pens.

457
00:33:50.027 --> 00:33:51.996
People think writers will need them.

458
00:33:51.997 --> 00:33:55.067
but they rarely use them nowadays.

459
00:33:55.396 --> 00:33:58.465
But they're too pretty and expensive to throw away.

460
00:33:58.466 --> 00:34:00.166
So they just end up keeping them somewhere.

461
00:34:00.636 --> 00:34:01.807
Then why are you buying one?

462
00:34:02.436 --> 00:34:04.736
Because she's the type who lingers on the stuff she hates...

463
00:34:04.737 --> 00:34:07.076
rather than what she likes.

464
00:34:07.077 --> 00:34:08.576
She'll never be able to forget it.

465
00:34:09.146 --> 00:34:10.706
I'd like to take a look at this one.

466
00:34:23.556 --> 00:34:25.056
I'm sorry.

467
00:34:25.396 --> 00:34:27.956
But we only have one left.

468
00:34:30.096 --> 00:34:31.836
Can I please take it?

469
00:34:31.837 --> 00:34:33.737
I waited three months for this.

470
00:34:34.496 --> 00:34:35.567
I...

471
00:34:36.967 --> 00:34:38.936
only have three months left.

472
00:34:42.177 --> 00:34:43.177
I'm...

473
00:34:44.876 --> 00:34:46.246
terminally ill.

474
00:34:46.576 --> 00:34:47.617
So...

475
00:34:48.646 --> 00:34:49.916
before I die.

476
00:34:51.047 --> 00:34:54.786
I want to buy something for my aunt.

477
00:35:07.096 --> 00:35:08.367
Stay strong.

478
00:35:09.666 --> 00:35:10.837
Thank you.

479
00:35:14.507 --> 00:35:15.646
Nice.

480
00:35:39.337 --> 00:35:42.907
I've never shopped like this in my entire life.

481
00:35:43.436 --> 00:35:45.337
I guess this is why people work so hard.

482
00:35:46.476 --> 00:35:48.206
- Who's next? - "Next"?

483
00:35:48.806 --> 00:35:50.507
The next person is me.

484
00:36:01.757 --> 00:36:04.626
I'm going to press on this to take a photo.

485
00:36:05.757 --> 00:36:07.725
I know you don't want to do this. but try to smile.

486
00:36:07.726 --> 00:36:09.326
It's not that I don't want to do it.

487
00:36:10.027 --> 00:36:11.297
But what's the purpose?

488
00:36:12.797 --> 00:36:14.837
- What? - To look at it from time to time?

489
00:36:16.536 --> 00:36:18.107
Then shouldn't I be the only one in the photo?

490
00:36:18.436 --> 00:36:20.205
Humans are really weird.

491
00:36:20.206 --> 00:36:21.946
Why make things like that?

492
00:36:21.947 --> 00:36:23.306
You never get to see them yourself.

493
00:36:23.976 --> 00:36:25.777
It's for others. not me.

494
00:36:27.246 --> 00:36:28.817
I'm like that sometimes.

495
00:36:31.757 --> 00:36:33.887
Who knows? I might not be the person looking at it later on.

496
00:36:38.826 --> 00:36:41.596
Just do it. I'm going to take the photo now.

497
00:36:41.967 --> 00:36:42.967
Smile.

498
00:36:54.137 --> 00:36:55.177
Here we go.

499
00:37:10.427 --> 00:37:11.757
When are you going to give everyone these gifts?

500
00:37:11.996 --> 00:37:14.056
What? I don't know.

501
00:37:14.757 --> 00:37:17.126
Maybe later. When I want to give it to them.

502
00:37:18.226 --> 00:37:19.697
Hey. give me your cell phone.

503
00:37:20.436 --> 00:37:21.867
Can't you see my hands are full?

504
00:37:26.576 --> 00:37:29.277
- What are you doing? - Just wait.

505
00:37:33.047 --> 00:37:34.146
Ta-Da.

506
00:37:35.587 --> 00:37:37.616
- Hey. - Your hands are full.

507
00:37:37.617 --> 00:37:38.786
So just stay still.

508
00:37:43.126 --> 00:37:44.126
See you.

509
00:37:44.726 --> 00:37:45.797
Dong Kyung.

510
00:37:47.326 --> 00:37:48.696
Just let it slide already.

511
00:37:48.697 --> 00:37:50.026
Do we really have to fight over something like this?

512
00:37:50.027 --> 00:37:51.796
As you already know. I can be pretty feisty.

513
00:37:51.797 --> 00:37:53.096
I'll see you later.

514
00:37:53.867 --> 00:37:55.507
Oh. later...

515
00:37:56.306 --> 00:37:58.637
What? Later? When?

516
00:38:18.726 --> 00:38:19.757
Hey.

517
00:38:28.067 --> 00:38:29.837
What is this? Am I dreaming?

518
00:38:30.306 --> 00:38:31.337
Yes.

519
00:38:33.837 --> 00:38:34.876
I guess it is a dream.

520
00:38:35.246 --> 00:38:37.846
You'd never take me to a place like this in real life.

521
00:38:39.646 --> 00:38:40.946
What's that supposed to mean?

522
00:38:40.947 --> 00:38:42.786
You said you never eat or sleep.

523
00:38:43.516 --> 00:38:46.556
I'm eating and sleeping right now just for you.

524
00:39:08.507 --> 00:39:11.746
Will I be able to taste everything even if it's a dream?

525
00:39:12.516 --> 00:39:14.646
I won't gain weight since it's a dream. right?

526
00:39:15.717 --> 00:39:17.547
- Are you happy? - No.

527
00:39:17.947 --> 00:39:20.087
It'd be better if we could do this in real life.

528
00:39:22.056 --> 00:39:23.826
There are some things that are only possible here.

529
00:39:24.056 --> 00:39:25.096
What?

530
00:39:36.337 --> 00:39:37.407
I'm sorry.

531
00:39:38.007 --> 00:39:39.176
Sorry we're late.

532
00:39:39.177 --> 00:39:41.375
Ji Na is such a rough driver.

533
00:39:41.376 --> 00:39:42.576
Hey. shut it.

534
00:39:43.246 --> 00:39:45.177
I guess I should've left you behind.

535
00:39:58.956 --> 00:40:01.197
It's my treat today. Eat as much as you want.

536
00:40:03.596 --> 00:40:05.196
- Thank you. - Enjoy.

537
00:40:05.197 --> 00:40:06.395
What's gotten into you?

538
00:40:06.396 --> 00:40:07.967
Hey. stop eating and ask for water.

539
00:40:10.666 --> 00:40:12.276
- Sun Kyung. eat up. - Okay.

540
00:40:12.277 --> 00:40:13.576
Eat up. kiddo.

541
00:40:16.407 --> 00:40:17.976
This is delicious.

542
00:41:16.806 --> 00:41:17.806
Good morning.

543
00:41:18.806 --> 00:41:20.677
Hey. you're awake. Come and eat.

544
00:41:23.246 --> 00:41:25.216
I called them over so they could eat with us.

545
00:41:25.217 --> 00:41:26.876
Why didn't you tell me your aunt came?

546
00:41:27.277 --> 00:41:28.547
So I told her instead.

547
00:41:28.846 --> 00:41:29.916
Right.

548
00:41:30.246 --> 00:41:31.617
Come and sit down.

549
00:41:32.487 --> 00:41:33.487
Okay.

550
00:41:33.717 --> 00:41:35.387
- Ta-Da. - My gosh.

551
00:41:36.186 --> 00:41:37.357
I haven't had a homemade meal in so long.

552
00:41:39.527 --> 00:41:41.656
When did you cook all this?

553
00:41:41.657 --> 00:41:42.766
This is your favourite.

554
00:41:43.297 --> 00:41:44.696
- Thank you for the food. - Thank you for the food.

555
00:41:44.697 --> 00:41:46.697
- Thank you. Auntie. - Enjoy.

556
00:41:57.246 --> 00:41:58.746
I'm getting changed.

557
00:41:59.547 --> 00:42:00.777
You can talk from there.

558
00:42:05.817 --> 00:42:07.387
I'm sorry I never listened to you.

559
00:42:08.157 --> 00:42:09.286
I'll listen from now on.

560
00:42:10.657 --> 00:42:13.526
This isn't a truce.

561
00:42:13.527 --> 00:42:14.556
I'm surrendering to you.

562
00:42:15.967 --> 00:42:16.967
Why?

563
00:42:17.967 --> 00:42:19.936
Are you going to try and become a nice kid?

564
00:42:21.396 --> 00:42:22.507
I'll give it a try.

565
00:42:23.967 --> 00:42:25.806
I'll try to prevent what you're worried about from happening.

566
00:42:27.706 --> 00:42:29.376
What is it that I'm worried about?

567
00:42:30.846 --> 00:42:32.717
She won't abandon the world.

568
00:42:33.016 --> 00:42:34.047
I'll make sure she doesn't.

569
00:42:34.146 --> 00:42:35.487
That's what I want.

570
00:42:40.617 --> 00:42:41.617
Also.

571
00:42:43.527 --> 00:42:45.126
I've always wanted to say this.

572
00:42:47.197 --> 00:42:49.467
I always felt sorry for you.

573
00:42:50.297 --> 00:42:53.666
I pitied you more than I resented you.

574
00:42:56.206 --> 00:42:57.806
Thanks for letting me be born.

575
00:43:00.436 --> 00:43:01.436
I've been...

576
00:43:03.107 --> 00:43:04.706
feeling that recently.

577
00:43:33.927 --> 00:43:36.398
What do you mean. she won't renew her contract?

578
00:43:39.197 --> 00:43:41.697
Tell me what you mean.

579
00:43:42.237 --> 00:43:43.637
It's as I said.

580
00:43:44.137 --> 00:43:45.567
She won't work with this company...

581
00:43:45.568 --> 00:43:47.366
unless Dong Kyung is her editor.

582
00:43:47.367 --> 00:43:49.177
Give me a break.

583
00:43:49.208 --> 00:43:51.107
Tell her to kiss off.

584
00:43:51.108 --> 00:43:54.747
Why is she so arrogant when she's not even popular?

585
00:43:54.748 --> 00:43:56.377
Fire Lee Hyun. Hey!

586
00:43:56.378 --> 00:43:58.346
Go and make it clear.

587
00:43:58.347 --> 00:44:01.617
"You're not rejecting us. I'm rejecting you. Me."

588
00:44:01.818 --> 00:44:03.056
That rude brat.

589
00:44:03.057 --> 00:44:05.886
- Dalgona won't work with us either. - What? Why not?

590
00:44:05.887 --> 00:44:08.227
Siberia and Jung Dang Myun too.

591
00:44:08.228 --> 00:44:09.326
What? Why?

592
00:44:09.327 --> 00:44:12.128
Same for Young Prince. whom she barely signed recently.

593
00:44:14.367 --> 00:44:16.696
What? No... We can't lose him.

594
00:44:16.697 --> 00:44:18.197
He's our top 10!

595
00:44:20.307 --> 00:44:21.667
Did you hear them?

596
00:44:21.668 --> 00:44:24.277
Mr. Cha. Do something.

597
00:44:24.278 --> 00:44:26.108
You'll do something. right?

598
00:44:27.778 --> 00:44:28.847
Like what?

599
00:44:29.177 --> 00:44:32.787
Either bring the writers or bring Dong Kyung.

600
00:44:32.847 --> 00:44:34.187
- Why should I? - What?

601
00:44:34.188 --> 00:44:36.657
You should take responsibility for something this important.

602
00:44:36.818 --> 00:44:38.458
What?

603
00:44:39.128 --> 00:44:42.257
Are you saying I created this mess. so I should clean it up?

604
00:44:42.258 --> 00:44:44.397
No. I'm saying the CEO should take responsibility...

605
00:44:44.398 --> 00:44:46.267
for something this important.

606
00:44:47.097 --> 00:44:49.398
At least you know you created this mess.

607
00:44:49.668 --> 00:44:51.137
I thought you didn't know.

608
00:44:53.568 --> 00:44:56.008
Call Dong Kyung right now.

609
00:44:59.677 --> 00:45:00.747
Answer me.

610
00:45:00.748 --> 00:45:01.777
You call her.

611
00:45:01.778 --> 00:45:04.617
She's screening my calls...

612
00:45:08.918 --> 00:45:11.418
Hey. kid. What did you just say?

613
00:45:15.898 --> 00:45:17.927
Do you see a kid in here?

614
00:45:19.568 --> 00:45:21.668
I assume the meeting is over. so we'll go now.

615
00:45:21.728 --> 00:45:25.608
We kids have too much work piled up.

616
00:45:38.787 --> 00:45:40.447
How dare he talk to the CEO like that?

617
00:45:48.387 --> 00:45:49.596
(Na Ji Na - Isn't it too sudden?)

618
00:45:49.597 --> 00:45:50.757
(Absolute obedience. Wait.)

619
00:45:50.758 --> 00:45:52.227
(Can you come right now? I'm stuck.)

620
00:45:52.228 --> 00:45:54.697
(Did you get home safely? I was too out of it earlier.)

621
00:45:56.798 --> 00:45:59.466
To be honest. I didn't expect the writers to do that.

622
00:45:59.467 --> 00:46:02.637
I know. I expected that from one writer. but...

623
00:46:02.978 --> 00:46:04.177
Lee Hyun?

624
00:46:06.878 --> 00:46:08.478
Did you get home safely?

625
00:46:08.847 --> 00:46:10.847
I was too out of it earlier.

626
00:46:22.798 --> 00:46:25.298
Mr. Cha. how do you know Lee Hyun?

627
00:46:26.298 --> 00:46:27.298
What?

628
00:46:27.528 --> 00:46:29.596
What is wrong with you today?

629
00:46:29.597 --> 00:46:31.237
During the meeting too.

630
00:46:31.697 --> 00:46:34.607
- What? - You've been checked out.

631
00:46:34.608 --> 00:46:36.938
Where are you? Are you somewhere nice?

632
00:46:38.407 --> 00:46:39.978
It's not that nice.

633
00:46:40.447 --> 00:46:43.217
How do you know Lee Hyun?

634
00:46:43.947 --> 00:46:45.648
Well...

635
00:46:45.987 --> 00:46:47.987
I filled in for Dong Kyung once at a meeting.

636
00:47:03.568 --> 00:47:05.438
- Where are you going? - I'm cutting.

637
00:47:08.237 --> 00:47:10.137
- Enjoy. - Thank you.

638
00:47:12.407 --> 00:47:13.608
Did you sober up?

639
00:47:14.407 --> 00:47:16.616
I've never been drunk in my entire life.

640
00:47:16.617 --> 00:47:17.747
I've been fine all morning.

641
00:47:17.748 --> 00:47:19.786
Is that why you called me "bro" and were informal with me?

642
00:47:19.787 --> 00:47:21.517
I'm sorry. sir. I think I was drunk.

643
00:47:22.148 --> 00:47:24.588
My tolerance is three shots of soju.

644
00:47:26.858 --> 00:47:27.858
Thanks.

645
00:47:28.387 --> 00:47:29.427
For what?

646
00:47:30.028 --> 00:47:31.597
For having a low tolerance?

647
00:47:31.827 --> 00:47:33.267
Just something.

648
00:47:38.697 --> 00:47:40.037
Oh. Hi.

649
00:47:40.668 --> 00:47:42.637
- Let's talk. - What would you like?

650
00:47:44.608 --> 00:47:45.647
I said let's talk.

651
00:47:45.648 --> 00:47:47.648
Your CEO is at a table behind you.

652
00:47:47.978 --> 00:47:49.177
Hyun Kyu.

653
00:47:50.177 --> 00:47:51.947
(Push)

654
00:47:54.847 --> 00:47:56.588
Look at this punk.

655
00:47:57.258 --> 00:48:00.427
Do you think I put you here so you can play all day?

656
00:48:00.758 --> 00:48:02.926
I have to go. The building owner just came in.

657
00:48:02.927 --> 00:48:04.327
I'll call you back later.

658
00:48:05.258 --> 00:48:07.028
Didn't you hear your dad?

659
00:48:07.298 --> 00:48:08.697
Why are you here?

660
00:48:10.498 --> 00:48:11.697
Mr. Cha.

661
00:48:12.438 --> 00:48:13.537
Dad?

662
00:48:19.248 --> 00:48:20.347
Father.

663
00:48:20.677 --> 00:48:22.378
Come on. Father.

664
00:48:22.717 --> 00:48:24.777
You should've told me you were coming.

665
00:48:24.778 --> 00:48:26.987
Whom did you come with? Did you come alone?

666
00:48:27.418 --> 00:48:28.617
Come on.

667
00:48:35.958 --> 00:48:36.998
Hey.

668
00:48:37.057 --> 00:48:38.457
Where are you rushing off to?

669
00:48:38.458 --> 00:48:40.898
Come on. Father. Don't be like that...

670
00:49:00.418 --> 00:49:02.818
What is wrong with you?

671
00:49:08.458 --> 00:49:10.798
He suddenly showed up at my door.

672
00:49:11.597 --> 00:49:13.367
Oh my gosh. Hyun Kyu?

673
00:49:13.597 --> 00:49:15.527
Was he always that aggressive?

674
00:49:15.528 --> 00:49:17.036
Time changes people.

675
00:49:17.037 --> 00:49:19.667
That's not the point. Who told him where I live?

676
00:49:19.668 --> 00:49:20.966
It wasn't me.

677
00:49:20.967 --> 00:49:23.037
Who else came over besides you?

678
00:50:03.677 --> 00:50:04.818
You said you wanted to talk.

679
00:50:06.487 --> 00:50:07.487
Yes.

680
00:50:08.387 --> 00:50:09.458
Go on.

681
00:50:11.688 --> 00:50:12.887
Let's talk upstairs.

682
00:50:16.958 --> 00:50:18.458
Do you know Na Ji Na?

683
00:50:24.338 --> 00:50:25.398
Yes.

684
00:50:28.907 --> 00:50:29.978
Is that all?

685
00:50:32.137 --> 00:50:33.608
Let's talk upstairs.

686
00:50:47.887 --> 00:50:49.128
I have to go somewhere.

687
00:51:00.708 --> 00:51:03.237
(Fill line. Quality may decrease if you cross this line.)

688
00:51:09.418 --> 00:51:10.477
(Mr. Cha Joo Ik)

689
00:51:10.478 --> 00:51:11.516
(Did you leave your umbrella?)

690
00:51:11.517 --> 00:51:14.148
(Incoming Call)

691
00:51:16.387 --> 00:51:18.287
- Hello? - Where are you?

692
00:51:19.157 --> 00:51:21.458
- Who... - It's me. Hyun Kyu.

693
00:51:23.028 --> 00:51:24.826
How did you get my number?

694
00:51:24.827 --> 00:51:26.767
I'll explain when I see you. Let's meet right now.

695
00:51:27.068 --> 00:51:28.097
Right now?

696
00:51:28.668 --> 00:51:30.967
- I'm not home. - Where are you?

697
00:51:31.838 --> 00:51:33.438
I'm at the laundromat by my apartment.

698
00:51:41.407 --> 00:51:43.318
- What are you doing? - Are you seeing anyone?

699
00:51:44.248 --> 00:51:46.188
- What? - Are you seeing anyone?

700
00:51:47.117 --> 00:51:48.617
- No. - Or are there any guys you like?

701
00:51:50.358 --> 00:51:51.688
Even if there are. date me.

702
00:51:54.458 --> 00:51:57.028
I don't care who that guy is. We met first.

703
00:51:57.758 --> 00:51:59.056
I liked you first.

704
00:51:59.057 --> 00:52:00.097
And...

705
00:52:02.169 --> 00:52:03.698
I still like you.

706
00:52:43.209 --> 00:52:45.609
We must put up with a lot of hassles now that we don't live together.

707
00:52:46.408 --> 00:52:47.448
Right.

708
00:52:51.548 --> 00:52:52.919
That should do it. Bye.

709
00:53:03.959 --> 00:53:06.298
What? You don't want to let go of my hand?

710
00:53:11.499 --> 00:53:13.008
If...

711
00:53:18.408 --> 00:53:19.548
What if...

712
00:53:22.209 --> 00:53:23.748
I wanted to live?

713
00:53:23.749 --> 00:53:25.618
Can you grant me that wish?

714
00:53:31.088 --> 00:53:32.118
No.

715
00:53:32.559 --> 00:53:35.488
I can't do that. My job is to destroy.

716
00:53:38.599 --> 00:53:39.629
I see.

717
00:53:42.169 --> 00:53:43.568
I knew it.

718
00:53:45.338 --> 00:53:47.008
I just wanted to ask.

719
00:53:52.749 --> 00:53:54.048
You heard it. didn't you?

720
00:53:55.908 --> 00:53:58.079
What everyone was thinking in their heads. right?

721
00:54:00.249 --> 00:54:01.888
It might look like...

722
00:54:03.388 --> 00:54:05.488
they are all smiling at me.

723
00:54:08.428 --> 00:54:09.528
But...

724
00:54:10.559 --> 00:54:11.959
they are hurting inside. right?

725
00:54:14.399 --> 00:54:15.499
As much as me.

726
00:54:17.468 --> 00:54:18.638
Or more.

727
00:54:23.838 --> 00:54:24.908
Yes.

728
00:54:30.519 --> 00:54:31.519
What about you?

729
00:54:37.419 --> 00:54:39.658
What goes in your head when you look at me?

730
00:54:41.329 --> 00:54:42.859
You think I can't see that?

731
00:54:44.129 --> 00:54:45.399
You keep...

732
00:54:47.568 --> 00:54:51.138
You keep hinting at me that I should live...

733
00:54:54.408 --> 00:54:56.579
when I only see death in your eyes.

734
00:55:02.149 --> 00:55:04.579
How do you think I feel when I see that?

735
00:55:06.888 --> 00:55:10.359
You can do what you had in mind from the beginning.

736
00:55:11.088 --> 00:55:12.218
It's simple as that.

737
00:55:16.999 --> 00:55:18.059
Bye.

738
00:55:47.959 --> 00:55:50.798
Its flowers were beautiful back in the day.

739
00:55:51.859 --> 00:55:53.629
I don't see any flowers these days.

740
00:55:54.698 --> 00:55:56.269
It's dying.

741
00:55:59.908 --> 00:56:01.169
Just like us.

742
00:56:03.709 --> 00:56:06.979
Both you and I are dying too.

743
00:56:09.778 --> 00:56:11.879
That's what it means to live.

744
00:56:14.488 --> 00:56:15.688
Goodness.

745
00:56:15.689 --> 00:56:17.658
I thought the flowers would always be around.

746
00:56:18.859 --> 00:56:20.859
What a shame now that I can't see them anymore.

747
00:56:22.388 --> 00:56:24.059
Its flowers were so beautiful.

748
00:56:33.609 --> 00:56:35.809
What goes in your head when you look at me?

749
00:56:38.209 --> 00:56:41.407
I thought I would be able to watch people disappear...

750
00:56:41.408 --> 00:56:43.218
to the end of time.

751
00:56:52.658 --> 00:56:53.959
Eating.

752
00:56:55.689 --> 00:56:56.999
sleeping.

753
00:57:00.629 --> 00:57:03.298
feeling compassionate. falling in love.

754
00:57:07.008 --> 00:57:09.137
and having a place to go...

755
00:57:09.138 --> 00:57:10.408
Is this how it feels to be human?

756
00:57:32.459 --> 00:57:34.669
Dissipating from the world didn't scare me.

757
00:57:51.649 --> 00:57:54.349
But not being able to see you anymore scared me.

758
00:58:16.039 --> 00:58:18.138
Like a fool. I just realized...

759
00:58:19.609 --> 00:58:23.118
that I don't have much time left.

760
00:58:26.888 --> 00:58:29.218
What's wrong? What happened?

761
00:58:38.859 --> 00:58:39.899
I love you.

762
00:58:44.868 --> 00:58:45.868
I am...

763
00:58:47.568 --> 00:58:48.939
in love with you.

764
00:59:28.508 --> 00:59:32.448
(Doom at Your Service)

765
00:59:32.818 --> 00:59:35.349
I decided to date him.

766
00:59:36.048 --> 00:59:38.818
Do you still feel lonely and alone?

767
00:59:39.658 --> 00:59:42.189
No. You're back.

768
00:59:42.658 --> 00:59:44.959
Hey. don't look at me like that.

769
00:59:45.629 --> 00:59:48.169
He's been scowling at us.

770
00:59:48.499 --> 00:59:50.168
You were like a puppy protecting his owner.

771
00:59:50.169 --> 00:59:51.499
You glared like this.

772
00:59:51.698 --> 00:59:53.539
I told Ji Na.

773
00:59:54.309 --> 00:59:55.338
Don't answer it.

774
00:59:56.209 --> 00:59:57.508
I need to talk to you.

775
00:59:58.238 --> 01:00:01.278
Be madly in love and live.

776
01:00:02.849 --> 01:00:05.048
I want to make a birthday wish.

777
01:00:05.778 --> 01:00:06.948
Will you marry me?

777
01:00:07.305 --> 01:01:07.753
